{"analytics_identifier":"OT1192","base_path":"/government/organisations/pubs-code-adjudicator","content_id":"08c7e23c-d822-406c-812b-3de9c03a0518","description":"PCA works with the Department for Business and Trade .","details":{"acronym":"PCA","alternative_format_contact_email":"office@pubscodeadjudicator.gov.uk","body":"<div class=\"govspeak\">\n<p><abbr title=\"Pubs Code Adjudicator\">PCA</abbr> works with the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/department-for-business-and-trade\">Department for Business and Trade</a>.</p>\n</div>","brand":null,"default_news_image":{"high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5ba4e42540f0b6053af73b6d/s960_Beer_pumps_and_Glasses_graphic__1_.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5ba4e425e5274a55e18d2bc4/s300_Beer_pumps_and_Glasses_graphic__1_.jpg"},"foi_exempt":false,"logo":{"crest":"single-identity","formatted_title":"Pubs Code Adjudicator"},"ordered_corporate_information_pages":[],"ordered_featured_documents":[{"document_type":"Transparency data","href":"/government/publications/pub-owning-businesses-compliance-reports-2023-24","image":{"alt_text":"Laptop","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/67ec0480e9c76fa33048c5f4/s712_Laptop_pic_resized.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/67ec0480199d1cd55b48c5f5/s465_Laptop_pic_resized.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/67ec04809eae202448299b37/Laptop_pic_resized.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2025-03-31T18:43:20.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>As part of our ongoing commitment to ensuring transparency and fairness in the tied pub sector, the Pubs Code Adjudicator (PCA) has released an overview of key aspects of the latest annual Compliance Reports submitted by regulated pub-owning businesses (POBs). We have also released an infographic on the total number of pubs code agreements and size of the regulated estate.</p>\n</div>","title":"Pub-Owning Businesses' Compliance Reports 2023-24"},{"document_type":"Corporate report","href":"/government/publications/pubs-code-adjudicator-pca-levy-methodology-for-2023-24","image":{"alt_text":"Menu board","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6645cbf9f34f9b5a56adc8ed/s712_Pubs_code_menu_board.png","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6645cbf9bd01f5ed32793cc9/s465_Pubs_code_menu_board.png","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6645cbf9b7249a4c6e9d3601/Pubs_code_menu_board.png"},"public_updated_at":"2024-05-13T14:59:22.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Section 63(1) of the Small Business, Enterprise and Employment Act 2015 (the Act) authorises the PCA to impose a levy on pub-owning businesses towards PCA’s expenses. Section 63(5) of the Act permits the PCA to vary the amount to be paid by pub-owning businesses, to reflect the expense and time that the PCA expects to spend in dealing with matters relating to them in the application of the Code. Before imposing the levy, the PCA must obtain the consent of the Secretary of State – section 63(2) of the Act.</p>\n</div>","title":"Pubs Code Adjudicator (PCA) Levy Methodology for 2023-24"},{"document_type":"Corporate report","href":"/government/publications/pca-annual-report-and-accounts-2022-2023","image":{"alt_text":"Report","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6581b755ed3c34000d3bfbcb/s712_report_pic_.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6581b75523b70a0013234c46/s465_report_pic_.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6581b755fc07f300128d44cd/report_pic_.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2023-12-19T12:49:55.000+00:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Information on the PCA’s performance and expenditure for the reporting period.</p>\n</div>","title":"PCA Annual Report and Accounts 2022-2023"},{"document_type":"Corporate report","href":"/government/publications/pubs-code-adjudicator-publishes-statutory-review-submission-for-the-period-april-2019-to-march-2022","image":{"alt_text":"","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6336e1cbd3bf7f34ec597873/s712_stat_review_pic_.png","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6336e1cbd3bf7f34f5e5d836/s465_stat_review_pic_.png","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/6336e1cbe90e0772e5d33e73/stat_review_pic_.png"},"public_updated_at":"2022-09-30T00:00:00.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The office of the Pubs Code Adjudicator has published its submission to the second statutory review of the Pubs Code and Adjudicator.</p>\n</div>","title":"Pubs Code Adjudicator publishes statutory review submission for the period April 2019 to March 2022"},{"document_type":"FOI release","href":"/government/publications/pubs-code-adjudicator-foi-responses-2023","image":{"alt_text":"laptop on a table","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/64cbb5aa995827000dc1e897/s712_Laptop_and_coffee2.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/64cbb5aa9958270010c1e899/s465_Laptop_and_coffee2.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/64cbb5aa3c4564000d9429b1/Laptop_and_coffee2.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2023-12-18T12:33:54.000+00:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Freedom of Information (FOI) responses to requests received by the Pubs Code Adjudicator (PCA) from January to December 2023</p>\n</div>","title":"Pubs Code Adjudicator FOI responses 2023"}],"ordered_featured_links":[{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/useful-information-and-forms/contact-information-and-forms","title":"Useful information and forms"},{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/pubs-code-factsheets","title":"Tenant factsheets"},{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/pubs-code-action",