 Pubs Code (including disputes on rent and market rent only options), investigate suspected systemic breaches of the Code more widely across the sector, provide advice and guidance about the Code and report on unfair business practices.</p>\n","role_payment_type":null},"document_type":"board_member_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2018-01-19T15:01:43Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Deputy Pubs Code Adjudicator","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2020-05-04T07:04:41Z","schema_name":"role_appointment","title":"Fiona Dickie - Deputy Pubs Code Adjudicator","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"2ab025bd-0e87-4208-9289-8bc25fbfebb6","details":{"current":true,"ended_on":null,"person_appointment_order":6193,"started_on":"2020-05-03T00:00:00+01:00"},"document_type":"role_appointment","links":{"role":[{"content_id":"5f35e375-7362-46a9-bb7a-abdfc64bb839","details":{"body":"<p>The Pubs Code regulates the relationship between all businesses owning 500 or more tied pubs in England and Wales and their tied tenants. The Adjudicator has powers to arbitrate individual disputes about breaches of the Pubs Code (including disputes on rent and market rent only options), investigate suspected systemic breaches of the Code more widely across the sector, and provide advice and guidance about the Code and report on unfair business practices.</p>\n","role_payment_type":null},"document_type":"board_member_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2020-05-04T07:25:15Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Pubs Code Adjudicator","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2020-05-04T07:03:34Z","schema_name":"role_appointment","title":"Fiona Dickie - Pubs Code Adjudicator","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2024-03-26T11:42:49Z","schema_name":"person","title":"Fiona Dickie","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/fiona-dickie","withdrawn":false}],"ordered_contacts":[{"content_id":"d9fe21f3-704d-4c57-aa27-e621e988e3b1","details":{"contact_form_links":[{"link":"https://www.rohs.bis.gov.uk/pca-enquiry/"}],"description":"If you have a query about the Pubs Code or an arbitration referral, you may find the answer in our helpful factsheets: https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/pubs-code-factsheets.\r\n\r\nAlternatively, complete our enquiry form, or send us an email. If you would prefer to discuss your enquiry, you can request a call back by telephoning the number above.\r\n\r\nPlease note: the PCA cannot deal with complaints about pubs. This includes concerns about pub staff or service.","email_addresses":[{"email":"office@pubscodeadjudicator.gov.uk","title":"Pubs Code Adjudicator"}],"phone_numbers":[{"number":"0800 528 8080","title":"Call back service"}],"post_addresses":[{"iso2_country_code":"gb","locality":"Birmingham","postal_code":"B2 4BJ","region":"England ","street_address":"4th Floor\r\n23 Stephenson Street\r\n","title":"Pubs Code Adjudicator","world_location":"United Kingdom"}],"title":"General enquiries"},"document_type":"contact","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2021-08-19T11:28:59Z","schema_name":"contact","title":"General enquiries","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"a215e227-242a-47c4-9b07-ef8fa4577ddc","details":{"contact_form_links":[{"link":"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pubs-code-how-to-refer-an-issue-to-the-adjudicator"}],"description":"Pubs Code arbitrations are managed by the Chartered Institute of Arbitrators (CIArb) on behalf of the PCA.  Full details, including how to pay the referral fee, can be found on their website: https://www.ciarb.org/disputes/schemes/pubs-code-adjudicator-arbitration-service\r\n\r\nThere is a difference between a general enquiry and a formal referral to the PCA for arbitration. You can only make a referral if you are a tied tenant (or a pub owning business in relation to market rent only disputes), or authorised to act on their behalf.","email_addresses":null,"phone_numbers":null,"post_addresses":[],"title"